-- China Investigates Export & Credit Insurance Company Losses, Observer Says
-- William Bi
-- 2010-07-17T02:45:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/china-investigates-export-credit-insurance-company-losses-observer-says.html

          
          
             China Export & Credit Insurance
Corp., a state-owned insurer of exports, is being investigated
by the Ministry of Finance for losses incurred from business
activities the last decade, the Economic Observer reported,
citing people familiar with the matter it didn’t identify. A
weekend telephone call placed to China Export & Credit seeking
their response to the report wasn’t answered.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
William Bi in Beijing at 
 wbi@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        